Kamar:	卡瑪：
Baddhi Slama:	巴迪·斯拉瑪：
What a blitz!  It looks like you lost yardage on that play.  Brothers: 6, %s: 0. 	好個快攻！看來你這一波輸慘了。兄弟隊：6，%s：0。
the man	那名男子
You kill me!	你真要笑死我了！
Kamar	卡瑪
He is wearing the uniform of a palace guard.  This is bad.  Very bad.	他穿著宮廷侍衛的制服。這下糟了，非常糟。
Jabbar	賈巴爾
the pots on the shelf	架上的陶罐
As the pieces of pottery hurtle towards you, you realize that you can't possibly catch them all.  Several fall to the floor, crashing loudly and alerting the old man.  The pottery was worthless, so your sentence is less severe than it might have been.  (They cut only one of your hands off.)	陶片朝你飛來，你發現自己根本接不完。有幾件摔落地面，發出巨響，驚動了老人。這些陶器不值錢，所以你的刑罰比原本輕一些。（他們只砍掉你一隻手。）
Give Me a Hand	助我一臂之力
the large rug	大地毯
The large rug is too large to steal.  It simply covers what's beneath it.	這張大地毯太大了，偷不走。它只是蓋著底下的東西。
the door to the alley	通往小巷的門
The heavy wooden door leads to the alley.	這扇厚重的木門通往小巷。
the drapes	布簾
Drapes cover a doorway which undoubtedly leads to the old man's bed chamber.	布簾遮住一道門，想必通往老人的臥房。
As it strikes the drapes, the sound frightens the old man.  He calls for his sons, who are angry.  VERY angry.  And violent.  VERY, VERY violent.	東西打中布簾發出的聲響嚇到了老人。他喊來兒子們，他們很生氣，非常生氣，而且很暴力，非常、非常暴力。
Painful, VERY Painful!	好痛，非常痛！
the trapdoor	活門
There appears to be a trapdoor built into the boards of the floor.	地板的木板上似乎裝有一扇活門。
Huh.  Kamar, your father is becoming senile.	哼，卡瑪，你父親越來越老糊塗了。
the small rug	小地毯
The small rug has an interesting pattern but not enough value to be worth lugging around.	這張小地毯的花紋很有趣，但價值不夠，不值得帶著到處跑。
the wardrobe doors	衣櫃門
The wardrobe doors are beautifully carved, but the hinges look a bit rusty.	衣櫃門雕工精美，但鉸鏈看起來有點生鏽。
The wardrobe doors are beautifully carved, but well-worn.	衣櫃門雕工精美，但已相當老舊。
No Stealing Aloud!	偷竊不得喧嘩！
the silver tea service	銀製茶具
The tea service is made of silver and looks very valuable.	這套茶具是純銀打造，看起來相當值錢。
the doorway	門口
The doorway is the only way out of the room.	這道門口是離開房間的唯一出路。
the shackles that bound you	綁住你的鐐銬
your fighting equipment	你的戰鬥裝備
